  "texts": [
    "This paper explores the application of RL in addressing resource allocation challenges within ERP systems, presenting a novel framework and evaluating its performance.",
    "Systems for enterprise resource planning, or ERP, are crucial tools for businesses to control and optimize a variety of corporate operations.Organizations can attain operational efficiency, improve decision-making, and sustain efficient resource management by integrating operations like finance, human resources, supply chain management, and production into a single platform.",
    "Resource allocation, which includes allocating resources (people, materials, equipment, and money) to tasks, projects, and departments as efficiently as possible, is one of the most important activities in ERP systems.",
    "In ERP systems, resource allocation has historically mostly depended on human judgment, historical data, and predetermined criteria.",
    "However, conventional approaches frequently fail as organizations get more intricate and their activities more dynamic."
